/************************************************************************************************
Program:  	    owf_CharacterToDecimal
Author:	        Alan Groves
Date created:	23/10/2022
											
Description:   

This function was specially written for the OWS Submission Header although it could be used generically.
The OWS Submission Header accepts numeric values into a nvarchar(4000) column
(sa_ows_QuestionnaireResponses.AnswerText). It is possible that this table column will contain bad data
that causes arithmetic conversion errors.

For example, these will error:
declare @var nvarchar(4000) = '' select convert(decimal(16,2),@var)
declare @var nvarchar(4000) = '.' select convert(decimal(16,2),@var)
declare @var nvarchar(4000) = '1,000.00' select convert(decimal(16,2),@var)
....but all these scenarios can be found in the OWS Submission Header.

Below are the algorithm steps of this function:
1) The function below always removes commas from the amount in flight as these cause errors.
2) It then checks to see if there are only digits and a decimal point in the number:
	a) If no, then it returns zero because it's a not a true number that will numerically convert.
	b) If yes, then it checks that the text value is not a blank field or a single decimal point
			and will successfully convert the text field (with commas removed) from a nvarchar(4000)
			value to a decimal(16,2) value.

Execute using the following command:
  select dbo.owf_CharacterToDecimal('1,000.00')

									
Amendment History								
-----------------								
											
Date			Who			    Description				
----------		-------------	-----------			
************************************************************************************************/

create function [dbo].[owf_CharacterToDecimal] (@Text nvarchar(4000))
returns decimal(16,2)
as

begin

	return  case when PATINDEX('%[^0-9.]%',replace(case when @Text in ('.','') then '0.0' else @Text end,',','')) > 0 
				then convert(decimal(16,2),0.0) 
				else convert(decimal(16,2),isnull(case when @Text in ('.','') then '0.0' else replace(@Text,',','') end,0.0)) 
			end
	
end




